00:00:08.776 --> 00:00:10.077 position:27% line:89% align:start
[birds chirping]

00:00:10.678 --> 00:00:12.312 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
We're totally broke.

00:00:13.113 --> 00:00:14.682 position:33% line:89% align:start
Oh, come on,

00:00:14.816 --> 00:00:16.651 position:10% line:83% align:start
seems like that's all you can
talk about these days, boss.

00:00:16.784 --> 00:00:20.020 position:10% line:83% align:start
So, I'm assuming that's what
we're here to discuss, right?

00:00:20.487 --> 00:00:22.055 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
It's been challenging

00:00:22.189 --> 00:00:24.191 position:27% line:83% align:start
trying to recover
after getting raided by bandits.

00:00:24.491 --> 00:00:26.528 position:19% line:83% align:start
The burden of reopening
the two villages we had

00:00:26.661 --> 00:00:28.763 position:33% line:83% align:start
to shut down
has proved a heavy one.

00:00:28.897 --> 00:00:30.230 position:21% line:89% align:start
Everyone has felt it.

00:00:31.498 --> 00:00:32.534 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:00:32.667 --> 00:00:34.368 position:24% line:83% align:start
Between digging up
the filled-in wells,

00:00:34.502 --> 00:00:35.770 position:10% line:89% align:start
rebuilding all the homesteads

00:00:35.904 --> 00:00:37.605 position:24% line:83% align:start
that were torn down
when everyone left,

00:00:37.739 --> 00:00:39.406 position:24% line:83% align:start
and securing food
for the villagers,

00:00:39.541 --> 00:00:41.341 position:16% line:83% align:start
so they could get through
the upcoming winter

00:00:41.475 --> 00:00:43.110 position:21% line:83% align:start
after having to strip
the fields,

00:00:43.611 --> 00:00:45.914 position:10% line:83% align:start
we're quickly running through
our treasury.

00:00:46.046 --> 00:00:47.549 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

00:00:47.682 --> 00:00:49.449 position:16% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE] It certainly
didn't help our situation any

00:00:49.584 --> 00:00:51.819 position:24% line:83% align:start
that we were forced
to let the bandit leader escape.

00:00:51.953 --> 00:00:54.054 position:7% line:83% align:start
Yeah, that really put us back,
didn't it?

00:00:54.187 --> 00:00:57.457 position:7% line:83% align:start
We would have secured at least
200 gold coins for his head.

00:00:57.592 --> 00:00:59.694 position:7% line:83% align:start
We can't just borrow the money,
can we?

00:00:59.827 --> 00:01:01.629 position:5% line:83% align:start
There's no one to lend us money,
though.

00:01:01.763 --> 00:01:03.497 position:33% line:83% align:start
Nearby fiefs
have nothing to spare

00:01:03.631 --> 00:01:05.633 position:7% line:83% align:start
after dealing with the problems
from the winter storms.

00:01:05.767 --> 00:01:08.068 position:16% line:83% align:start
The neighboring villages
were so badly damaged

00:01:08.201 --> 00:01:10.304 position:35% line:83% align:start
by bandits
they're asking us for loans!

00:01:10.437 --> 00:01:11.873 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
What about the court nobles?

00:01:12.006 --> 00:01:13.841 position:19% line:89% align:start
Ah! There's no chance!

00:01:13.975 --> 00:01:16.778 position:7% line:83% align:start
Loans from those stingy misers
is an even worse idea.

00:01:16.911 --> 00:01:20.080 position:13% line:83% align:start
Each gold piece would come
with a hundred more in interest.

00:01:20.213 --> 00:01:21.081 position:41% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Right.

00:01:21.214 --> 00:01:22.650 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Hm?
-Hm?

00:01:22.784 --> 00:01:23.985 position:21% line:83% align:start
There must be someone
who could can help us there.

00:01:24.151 --> 00:01:25.520 position:24% line:89% align:start
Is there any chance

00:01:25.653 --> 00:01:27.120 position:16% line:83% align:start
you and mother could ask
your parents for assistance?

00:01:27.254 --> 00:01:28.756 position:13% line:89% align:start
That's not going to happen.

00:01:28.890 --> 00:01:31.124 position:19% line:83% align:start
We've already cut ties
with both sides.

00:01:31.258 --> 00:01:33.427 position:10% line:89% align:start
It's been well over a decade.

00:01:33.561 --> 00:01:36.396 position:7% line:83% align:start
I've never even introduced them
to their grandchildren.

00:01:36.531 --> 00:01:37.732 position:13% line:89% align:start
So, I can't exactly show up

00:01:37.865 --> 00:01:39.801 position:30% line:83% align:start
and just demand
they give me money.

00:01:39.934 --> 00:01:41.301 position:19% line:89% align:start
Yeah, that makes sense.

00:01:41.803 --> 00:01:44.404 position:13% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE] Back when your
mother and I first got together,

00:01:44.539 --> 00:01:47.341 position:7% line:83% align:start
the lands were even more barren
than they are now

00:01:47.474 --> 00:01:50.578 position:19% line:83% align:start
and everyone around us
opposed our union as well.

00:01:50.712 --> 00:01:52.747 position:35% line:83% align:start
Yep, after
their whirlwind love affair,

00:01:52.880 --> 00:01:55.550 position:16% line:83% align:start
they pretty much ran away
somewhere to secretly elope!

00:01:55.683 --> 00:01:57.619 position:7% line:89% align:start
Gotta say, I'm pretty jealous!

00:01:57.752 --> 00:01:58.553 position:30% line:89% align:start
[clears throat]

00:01:58.686 --> 00:02:00.021 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Arranged marriages

00:02:00.153 --> 00:02:01.455 position:24% line:83% align:start
are still the norm
in this world,

00:02:01.589 --> 00:02:03.457 position:19% line:83% align:start
so that must have been
a struggle for them.

00:02:03.591 --> 00:02:05.459 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
Anyway, we have no money!

00:02:05.593 --> 00:02:07.862 position:19% line:83% align:start
[FEUILLE] Yeah, I think
you've made that crystal clear!

00:02:07.996 --> 00:02:09.697 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckles]

00:02:09.831 --> 00:02:11.465 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:02:11.599 --> 00:02:14.434 position:13% line:83% align:start
[NARRATOR] This is the tale
of a genius patissier

00:02:14.569 --> 00:02:16.738 position:21% line:83% align:start
whose dream of making
the world's greatest dessert

00:02:16.871 --> 00:02:18.072 position:30% line:89% align:start
was cut short.

00:02:18.205 --> 00:02:19.874 position:24% line:83% align:start
Now, reincarnated
into another realm

00:02:20.008 --> 00:02:21.375 position:13% line:89% align:start
as the son of a poor noble.

00:02:21.509 --> 00:02:24.679 position:24% line:83% align:start
He pursues a world
full of desserts and smiles!

00:02:24.812 --> 00:02:28.482 position:13% line:83% align:start
A tale that's syrupy sweet,
chock full of yummy treats

00:02:28.616 --> 00:02:31.184 position:33% line:83% align:start
and sprinkled
with bitter darkness.

00:02:31.318 --> 00:02:33.487 position:10% line:89% align:start
A pastry chef, who was reborn

00:02:33.621 --> 00:02:36.323 position:19% line:83% align:start
and dreams of creating
this new world's

00:02:36.456 --> 00:02:38.893 position:16% line:89% align:start
very own land of sweets!

00:04:11.152 --> 00:04:12.120 position:35% line:59% align:start
[PAS] Hmm.

00:04:12.252 --> 00:04:13.755 position:7% line:65% align:start
So that's what's been up, huh?

00:04:13.888 --> 00:04:15.723 position:10% line:59% align:start
You guys have been discussing
all of this stuff

00:04:15.857 --> 00:04:17.290 position:7% line:65% align:start
in your dad's office for days?

00:04:17.424 --> 00:04:18.960 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yeah.

00:04:19.093 --> 00:04:22.163 position:16% line:83% align:start
You know, it's not honest
to keep secrets from us, Pas.

00:04:22.295 --> 00:04:23.998 position:13% line:89% align:start
That's "dishonest," Moron.

00:04:24.132 --> 00:04:25.733 position:19% line:89% align:start
Duh, yeah, I know that!

00:04:25.867 --> 00:04:27.969 position:10% line:89% align:start
Lumi, how are you healing up?

00:04:28.102 --> 00:04:30.104 position:24% line:83% align:start
Is it okay for you
to be out here right now?

00:04:30.238 --> 00:04:33.074 position:21% line:83% align:start
Yeah, Dad and Grandpa
both said I was good to go,

00:04:33.207 --> 00:04:35.176 position:7% line:89% align:start
so here I am, toughing it out!

00:04:35.308 --> 00:04:40.280 position:7% line:83% align:start
Ow, that hurts. The pain's not
really all gone yet.

00:04:40.413 --> 00:04:42.449 position:38% line:83% align:start
Watch it.
You're gonna overdo it.

00:04:42.583 --> 00:04:44.051 position:21% line:89% align:start
Oh, c'mon, I'm fine!

00:04:44.185 --> 00:04:46.453 position:33% line:83% align:start
-[Pas laughs]
-huh? What's so funny, Pas?

00:04:46.587 --> 00:04:49.157 position:33% line:83% align:start
You two make
the cutest little couple!

00:04:49.289 --> 00:04:50.591 position:5% line:89% align:start
I told you, it aren't like that!

00:04:50.725 --> 00:04:52.827 position:7% line:83% align:start
How about you shut your mouth,
huh?

00:04:53.861 --> 00:04:56.631 position:19% line:83% align:start
[MARC] So, why can't we
just make the fields bigger?

00:04:56.764 --> 00:04:58.966 position:10% line:83% align:start
[PAS] It's true that we still
have plenty of extra land

00:04:59.100 --> 00:05:00.300 position:27% line:89% align:start
we can cultivate.

00:05:00.433 --> 00:05:02.503 position:35% line:83% align:start
Of course,
it takes time to do that

00:05:02.637 --> 00:05:04.772 position:33% line:83% align:start
and manpower,
and most of all money.

00:05:04.906 --> 00:05:07.041 position:10% line:83% align:start
Plus, there's no way to do it
on short notice.

00:05:07.175 --> 00:05:08.308 position:33% line:89% align:start
Hey, I know!

00:05:08.441 --> 00:05:10.077 position:16% line:83% align:start
How about that bonka pie
you made for us?

00:05:10.211 --> 00:05:11.478 position:35% line:89% align:start
Bonka pie?

00:05:12.312 --> 00:05:15.850 position:10% line:83% align:start
It was so delicious! Why not
try selling them in town?

00:05:15.983 --> 00:05:17.051 position:44% line:89% align:start
Wow.

00:05:17.185 --> 00:05:19.821 position:41% line:83% align:start
I admit
they're a lot of fun to make.

00:05:19.954 --> 00:05:23.124 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:05:23.257 --> 00:05:26.060 position:21% line:83% align:start
There's nothing quite
like making a good dessert.

00:05:28.996 --> 00:05:30.031 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:05:30.164 --> 00:05:31.498 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:05:31.632 --> 00:05:33.400 position:19% line:83% align:start
[PAS] No, no! Stop it!
We're here to make money!

00:05:33.534 --> 00:05:35.269 position:13% line:83% align:start
In order to produce enough
to make a profit,

00:05:35.402 --> 00:05:38.272 position:10% line:83% align:start
we'd need to figure out a way
to bring in a lot of bonkas.

00:05:38.405 --> 00:05:40.373 position:7% line:89% align:start
So, it probably wouldn't work.

00:05:40.508 --> 00:05:42.009 position:33% line:89% align:start
In that case,

00:05:42.143 --> 00:05:44.245 position:7% line:83% align:start
why haven't you ever considered
teaching magic, then?

00:05:44.377 --> 00:05:47.048 position:19% line:83% align:start
Why are you so obsessed
with learning magic anyway?

00:05:47.181 --> 00:05:50.651 position:21% line:83% align:start
If I could use magic,
I'd be sure to do something epic

00:05:50.785 --> 00:05:54.889 position:16% line:83% align:start
like, become a rich noble
and eat yummy food all day long!

00:05:55.022 --> 00:05:55.857 position:33% line:89% align:start
What a joke!

00:05:55.990 --> 00:05:57.091 position:41% line:89% align:start
[yells]

00:05:57.225 --> 00:05:58.693 position:30% line:83% align:start
There's no way
you believe that'll happen.

00:05:58.826 --> 00:06:00.628 position:24% line:83% align:start
You'd for sure need
a miracle to learn magic

00:06:00.761 --> 00:06:02.663 position:24% line:83% align:start
and even if you did
figure out how to use it,

00:06:02.797 --> 00:06:05.733 position:19% line:83% align:start
there's no way you'd be
able to master it, anyway, Marc.

00:06:05.867 --> 00:06:07.535 position:10% line:89% align:start
What's that supposed to mean?

00:06:07.668 --> 00:06:09.303 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'm just being honest with you.

00:06:09.436 --> 00:06:11.172 position:21% line:83% align:start
If you ever did learn
a fire spell,

00:06:11.305 --> 00:06:12.840 position:5% line:89% align:start
you'd just set yourself on fire!

00:06:12.974 --> 00:06:14.909 position:16% line:83% align:start
'Cause you're as moronic
as they come!

00:06:15.042 --> 00:06:17.945 position:16% line:83% align:start
Hey, why'd you say that?
Stop making fun of me!

00:06:18.079 --> 00:06:19.046 position:33% line:89% align:start
Simmer down.

00:06:19.180 --> 00:06:20.314 position:16% line:83% align:start
Enough with the flirting
and what not.

00:06:20.447 --> 00:06:21.849 position:13% line:89% align:start
It ain't flirting, damn it!

00:06:21.983 --> 00:06:24.484 position:19% line:83% align:start
You know, I still think
magic might be the key.

00:06:24.619 --> 00:06:26.654 position:21% line:89% align:start
Huh! Oh, wow, really?

00:06:26.787 --> 00:06:30.157 position:10% line:83% align:start
Anyway, I want you to show us
that spell you use, Pas.

00:06:30.291 --> 00:06:31.525 position:16% line:89% align:start
Maybe we'll get inspired.

00:06:31.659 --> 00:06:33.227 position:30% line:89% align:start
Yeah, let's go!

00:06:33.361 --> 00:06:34.962 position:47% line:89% align:start
Mm!

00:06:35.329 --> 00:06:37.999 position:7% line:83% align:start
[PAS] They do say, "three heads
are better than one."

00:06:38.132 --> 00:06:40.601 position:19% line:83% align:start
Maybe this'll point me
in the right direction!

00:06:40.935 --> 00:06:42.637 position:19% line:83% align:start
When I was thinking up
brand new desserts

00:06:42.770 --> 00:06:45.373 position:21% line:83% align:start
back in my old world,
I was so obsessed,

00:06:45.506 --> 00:06:46.707 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'd stay up all night

00:06:46.841 --> 00:06:48.776 position:33% line:83% align:start
brainstorming
with my fellow chefs!

00:06:50.144 --> 00:06:51.979 position:19% line:89% align:start
All right. Let's do it.

00:06:52.113 --> 00:06:53.047 position:27% line:89% align:start
Go ahead and draw

00:06:53.180 --> 00:06:54.649 position:21% line:83% align:start
whatever you want to
in the dirt.

00:06:54.782 --> 00:06:56.350 position:19% line:89% align:start
So, just draw anything?

00:06:56.483 --> 00:06:57.752 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's right.

00:06:58.953 --> 00:07:01.088 position:38% line:89% align:start
[humming]

00:07:01.222 --> 00:07:02.356 position:38% line:89% align:start
[giggles]

00:07:02.489 --> 00:07:04.125 position:27% line:89% align:start
What's that? Huh?

00:07:04.258 --> 00:07:05.793 position:38% line:89% align:start
[laughs]

00:07:05.927 --> 00:07:09.664 position:7% line:83% align:start
[MARC] It's me, using my magic
to totally slay a dragon!

00:07:09.797 --> 00:07:12.266 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Oh, is that a dragon?

00:07:12.400 --> 00:07:13.868 position:47% line:89% align:start
Uh?

00:07:14.001 --> 00:07:16.170 position:13% line:83% align:start
I thought it was a drawing
of a weird worm with legs.

00:07:16.504 --> 00:07:17.437 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh.

00:07:17.571 --> 00:07:18.839 position:35% line:89% align:start
[laughing]

00:07:18.973 --> 00:07:21.175 position:33% line:83% align:start
Oh, hey Lumi,
that's a bonka, isn't it?

00:07:21.309 --> 00:07:22.643 position:24% line:89% align:start
Sure is! [giggles]

00:07:22.777 --> 00:07:24.345 position:21% line:89% align:start
Pretty sweet, right?

00:07:24.477 --> 00:07:25.846 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
What's that next to it?

00:07:25.980 --> 00:07:27.782 position:13% line:89% align:start
A hot bonka pie, obviously!

00:07:27.915 --> 00:07:31.352 position:16% line:83% align:start
[laughs] You suck so bad,
I thought it was a rock, geez.

00:07:31.519 --> 00:07:32.720 position:30% line:89% align:start
Uh, excuse me?

00:07:32.853 --> 00:07:34.454 position:21% line:83% align:start
Yours just looks like
a creepy snake

00:07:34.588 --> 00:07:36.123 position:5% line:89% align:start
slithering around on the ground.

00:07:36.257 --> 00:07:37.792 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Shut it.
-[growls]

00:07:37.925 --> 00:07:39.794 position:16% line:83% align:start
You just can't appreciate
how fire my dragon really is!

00:07:39.927 --> 00:07:41.729 position:27% line:83% align:start
Only a little kid
would say that!

00:07:41.862 --> 00:07:43.097 position:38% line:89% align:start
Cool it!

00:07:43.230 --> 00:07:45.599 position:10% line:83% align:start
How about I just demonstrate
my spell for you guys?

00:07:47.101 --> 00:07:48.436 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah?

00:07:48.569 --> 00:07:49.503 position:35% line:89% align:start
Replicate!

00:07:49.637 --> 00:07:50.738 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Hm?
-Hm?

00:07:50.871 --> 00:07:53.307 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh!

00:07:53.441 --> 00:07:55.876 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh!

00:07:56.010 --> 00:08:00.548 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:08:01.182 --> 00:08:02.049 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh!

00:08:02.183 --> 00:08:03.017 position:38% line:89% align:start
[screams]

00:08:03.150 --> 00:08:04.118 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:08:04.251 --> 00:08:08.189 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:08:08.322 --> 00:08:09.623 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:08:09.757 --> 00:08:13.394 position:21% line:83% align:start
Oh! That's so wicked!
Now, my drawing's on me.

00:08:13.527 --> 00:08:14.962 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's crazy!

00:08:15.096 --> 00:08:17.465 position:19% line:83% align:start
So, you really do know
how to use magic, don't you Pas?

00:08:17.598 --> 00:08:19.967 position:19% line:83% align:start
Well, you have seen me
use it before.

00:08:22.203 --> 00:08:23.537 position:41% line:83% align:start
[LUMI]
It's not rubbing off.

00:08:23.971 --> 00:08:26.741 position:19% line:83% align:start
Oh, yeah, it fades away
in three-ish days on skin.

00:08:27.174 --> 00:08:29.977 position:13% line:83% align:start
But it's permanent on trees
and walls, and stuff.

00:08:30.111 --> 00:08:32.013 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's like the coolest trick
ever!

00:08:32.146 --> 00:08:32.913 position:38% line:89% align:start
[laughs]

00:08:33.047 --> 00:08:34.849 position:7% line:89% align:start
I wanna show it to my Grandpa!

00:08:35.549 --> 00:08:38.185 position:38% line:83% align:start
Hey, Pas,
can you do the opposite?

00:08:38.319 --> 00:08:39.286 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh!

00:08:39.420 --> 00:08:41.088 position:24% line:89% align:start
Well, um, like how?

00:08:42.089 --> 00:08:44.692 position:10% line:83% align:start
Instead of copying a drawing
onto something,

00:08:44.825 --> 00:08:47.461 position:24% line:83% align:start
could you transfer
something else into a drawing?

00:08:47.595 --> 00:08:49.663 position:16% line:83% align:start
[PAS] Transfer something
into a drawing?

00:08:49.797 --> 00:08:51.065 position:19% line:83% align:start
Like putting the image
of a house

00:08:51.198 --> 00:08:53.067 position:21% line:83% align:start
or of someone's face
onto the ground?

00:08:53.768 --> 00:08:55.669 position:13% line:83% align:start
I think that'd be something
pretty special.

00:08:55.803 --> 00:08:58.039 position:19% line:83% align:start
That don't make a dang
lick of sense, Lumi!

00:08:58.172 --> 00:09:00.274 position:27% line:83% align:start
-[LUMI] You dork.
-[MARC] What'd you say?

00:09:00.408 --> 00:09:01.242 position:41% line:83% align:start
[LUMI]
Mega-dork!

00:09:01.375 --> 00:09:02.243 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Marc yells]

00:09:02.376 --> 00:09:04.445 position:27% line:89% align:start
Wait, that's it!

00:09:04.578 --> 00:09:08.682 position:27% line:83% align:start
Oh, wow perfect!
Lumi, you're a genius!

00:09:09.183 --> 00:09:10.785 position:35% line:89% align:start
[whimpers]

00:09:10.918 --> 00:09:13.287 position:5% line:89% align:start
Hey, where'd all this come from?

00:09:13.421 --> 00:09:14.722 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:09:14.855 --> 00:09:16.457 position:21% line:83% align:start
Sorry, I put my hands
on your wife, Marc.

00:09:16.590 --> 00:09:18.659 position:13% line:89% align:start
That gag's played out, Pas.

00:09:18.793 --> 00:09:22.329 position:19% line:83% align:start
But you may've given me
a really great idea!

00:09:24.065 --> 00:09:28.235 position:21% line:83% align:start
I see. The situation
with our finances is that dire?

00:09:28.369 --> 00:09:29.770 position:41% line:89% align:start
Mm-hmm.

00:09:29.904 --> 00:09:32.940 position:16% line:83% align:start
But still, I'm not sure
we can rely on my family

00:09:33.074 --> 00:09:35.042 position:10% line:89% align:start
to offer us much assistance.

00:09:35.176 --> 00:09:36.243 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

00:09:36.377 --> 00:09:38.479 position:13% line:89% align:start
I understand. Makes sense.

00:09:39.046 --> 00:09:40.515 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Great news!

00:09:40.881 --> 00:09:43.184 position:19% line:83% align:start
I've come up with a way
to make some money!

00:09:43.317 --> 00:09:46.353 position:24% line:83% align:start
Oh, yeah? Spill it.
What's your idea?

00:09:46.487 --> 00:09:48.722 position:24% line:83% align:start
Father, you told me
about your attempts

00:09:48.856 --> 00:09:50.925 position:5% line:83% align:start
to arrange a marriage for Josie,
right?

00:09:51.358 --> 00:09:52.593 position:41% line:89% align:start
I did.

00:09:52.726 --> 00:09:54.929 position:38% line:83% align:start
[FEUILLE]
Little lady's 13 years old.

00:09:55.062 --> 00:09:57.431 position:27% line:83% align:start
Just about right
for marriage arrangement!

00:09:57.566 --> 00:10:00.434 position:24% line:83% align:start
Since you can move
with your teleportation spell,

00:10:00.569 --> 00:10:02.837 position:10% line:83% align:start
you probably try to take her
everywhere you can

00:10:02.970 --> 00:10:05.172 position:5% line:83% align:start
to introduce her to new suitors,
right?

00:10:05.840 --> 00:10:07.074 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
Yes.

00:10:07.208 --> 00:10:08.742 position:27% line:83% align:start
I'm always happy
for the chance to show off

00:10:08.876 --> 00:10:11.178 position:30% line:83% align:start
how proud I am
of my beautiful daughter.

00:10:11.312 --> 00:10:12.847 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
But then,

00:10:12.980 --> 00:10:15.683 position:16% line:83% align:start
what do parents who can't
utilize that sort of magic do?

00:10:16.217 --> 00:10:16.951 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:10:17.084 --> 00:10:18.819 position:10% line:89% align:start
The most effective strategy,

00:10:18.953 --> 00:10:21.455 position:13% line:83% align:start
well, I guess that would be
attending a royal banquet

00:10:21.590 --> 00:10:22.990 position:30% line:89% align:start
at the capital.

00:10:23.124 --> 00:10:25.826 position:19% line:83% align:start
That's true, but travel
can prove so dangerous.

00:10:25.960 --> 00:10:28.329 position:41% line:83% align:start
Right,
and it's definitely not cheap!

00:10:28.462 --> 00:10:30.431 position:24% line:83% align:start
That's why they say
that when a noble travels,

00:10:30.565 --> 00:10:33.400 position:13% line:83% align:start
their money sprouts wings.
And flies away!

00:10:33.535 --> 00:10:34.935 position:35% line:89% align:start
With that,

00:10:35.069 --> 00:10:37.304 position:5% line:83% align:start
I was wondering if we could sell
something like this?

00:10:38.205 --> 00:10:39.373 position:35% line:89% align:start
Replicate.

00:10:44.078 --> 00:10:45.312 position:44% line:89% align:start
Wow!

00:10:45.446 --> 00:10:47.214 position:33% line:89% align:start
Look at that!

00:10:48.182 --> 00:10:49.683 position:13% line:89% align:start
What? Looks just like her!

00:10:49.817 --> 00:10:52.286 position:16% line:83% align:start
It's almost like looking
in a mirror!

00:10:52.419 --> 00:10:55.322 position:7% line:83% align:start
[PAC] I've decided to call them
"matchmaking photos."

00:10:55.456 --> 00:10:57.925 position:33% line:83% align:start
"Ask the heir
to the Fief of Morteln

00:10:58.058 --> 00:11:00.060 position:27% line:83% align:start
to use his magic
to make you a photo,

00:11:00.194 --> 00:11:01.896 position:5% line:89% align:start
and you can show off your child,

00:11:02.029 --> 00:11:04.431 position:16% line:83% align:start
but without ever needing
to travel anywhere."

00:11:04.798 --> 00:11:06.901 position:13% line:83% align:start
So, that could be our pitch
to parents

00:11:07.034 --> 00:11:10.237 position:13% line:83% align:start
seeking arranged marriages!
How about it, Father?

00:11:11.372 --> 00:11:13.508 position:16% line:83% align:start
I guess having knowledge
unrelated to sweets

00:11:13.642 --> 00:11:15.442 position:13% line:89% align:start
really comes in handy, too!

00:11:15.943 --> 00:11:17.144 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
Hmm.

00:11:17.278 --> 00:11:19.213 position:16% line:83% align:start
With such skillfully done
portraits,

00:11:19.346 --> 00:11:22.584 position:24% line:83% align:start
we could fetch five
or even ten gold coins!

00:11:22.716 --> 00:11:24.351 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's far cheaper than a painting

00:11:24.485 --> 00:11:27.656 position:16% line:83% align:start
and being made from magic
means no fees for materials.

00:11:27.788 --> 00:11:29.423 position:27% line:83% align:start
Plenty of parents
would pay out the nose

00:11:29.558 --> 00:11:32.760 position:5% line:83% align:start
just for the chance to introduce
their child with a picture.

00:11:33.562 --> 00:11:34.529 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckles]

00:11:34.663 --> 00:11:35.996 position:21% line:89% align:start
This just might work.

00:11:36.130 --> 00:11:39.601 position:16% line:83% align:start
Wait, wouldn't that mean
exposing Pas' magic?

00:11:39.733 --> 00:11:41.168 position:33% line:89% align:start
Seems risky.

00:11:41.302 --> 00:11:43.871 position:16% line:83% align:start
[PAS] It's not something
we'll be able to hide forever.

00:11:44.606 --> 00:11:46.073 position:21% line:89% align:start
It's not a bad idea.

00:11:46.207 --> 00:11:48.342 position:19% line:83% align:start
If we let people think
my magic is just used

00:11:48.475 --> 00:11:50.444 position:21% line:83% align:start
for making pictures,
it's a good cover story,

00:11:50.579 --> 00:11:53.113 position:13% line:83% align:start
and might allow me to hide
in plain sight.

00:11:53.247 --> 00:11:55.382 position:30% line:83% align:start
Pictures, huh?
I guess I can see it.

00:11:55.517 --> 00:11:56.917 position:41% line:89% align:start
Right.

00:11:57.051 --> 00:11:58.452 position:13% line:83% align:start
Let's start by feeling out
Count Retes about it.

00:11:58.587 --> 00:12:00.287 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Pas, my love?
-Yes, Mom?

00:12:00.421 --> 00:12:01.590 position:21% line:89% align:start
Just look right here.

00:12:01.722 --> 00:12:02.990 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:12:03.123 --> 00:12:06.060 position:24% line:83% align:start
These crow's feet.
Could you erase them?

00:12:07.629 --> 00:12:08.963 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh...

00:12:10.632 --> 00:12:12.132 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Count Retes' domain

00:12:12.266 --> 00:12:14.935 position:13% line:83% align:start
is in the southern reaches
of the Holy Kingdom of Praulich.

00:12:15.069 --> 00:12:18.305 position:19% line:83% align:start
It's a remote location,
facing the sea on two sides.

00:12:18.439 --> 00:12:21.075 position:24% line:83% align:start
Within its borders,
there are four main villages

00:12:21.208 --> 00:12:23.712 position:16% line:83% align:start
and over 50 smaller ones,
as well.

00:12:24.178 --> 00:12:25.680 position:24% line:83% align:start
[PAS] Roads connect
all of the villages

00:12:25.813 --> 00:12:29.049 position:21% line:83% align:start
to the local capital,
which also presides over them.

00:12:29.183 --> 00:12:31.620 position:7% line:83% align:start
It's one of the largest domains
in the south.

00:12:32.554 --> 00:12:36.890 position:13% line:59% align:start
And at the center of it all
is the local capital, Retesvale.

00:12:37.024 --> 00:12:38.225 position:19% line:89% align:start
I have come here today

00:12:38.359 --> 00:12:40.261 position:27% line:83% align:start
seeking a meeting
with Count Retes.

00:12:40.394 --> 00:12:44.231 position:7% line:83% align:start
I ask for safe passage within.
We've been expecting you.

00:12:44.566 --> 00:12:47.334 position:10% line:83% align:start
I wonder if he has come here
to express his displeasure

00:12:47.468 --> 00:12:49.604 position:30% line:83% align:start
at our failure
to crush the bandit threat?

00:12:49.738 --> 00:12:52.172 position:21% line:83% align:start
[COATON] Chastisement
from a mere backwater noble

00:12:52.306 --> 00:12:55.075 position:24% line:83% align:start
is nothing to fear,
at least not for you, I assume?

00:12:55.209 --> 00:12:57.244 position:41% line:83% align:start
[RETES]
Hmm. Perhaps so.

00:12:57.778 --> 00:13:01.482 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'll butter him up and send him
on his way back to the country.

00:13:05.419 --> 00:13:08.489 position:38% line:83% align:start
My Lady,
the Lord of Morteln has arrived.

00:13:08.856 --> 00:13:10.157 position:41% line:83% align:start
[RETES]
Allow him in.

00:13:11.392 --> 00:13:13.494 position:30% line:83% align:start
We are pleased
to have you join us, milord.

00:13:13.628 --> 00:13:15.963 position:24% line:83% align:start
It is such an honor
to finally get to meet

00:13:16.096 --> 00:13:17.798 position:13% line:89% align:start
the famous Lord of Morteln.

00:13:17.931 --> 00:13:20.267 position:10% line:65% align:start
Brioche Salgrade Mille Retes.

00:13:20.401 --> 00:13:24.171 position:21% line:59% align:start
I serve as the holder
of the borderland fief of Retes.

00:13:25.906 --> 00:13:27.241 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
Listen to me, Pas.

00:13:27.374 --> 00:13:29.443 position:35% line:83% align:start
Lady Retes
is the eldest daughter

00:13:29.577 --> 00:13:31.011 position:16% line:89% align:start
of the late Count Retes.

00:13:31.145 --> 00:13:33.280 position:27% line:83% align:start
Her predecessors
died in conflict,

00:13:33.414 --> 00:13:36.050 position:16% line:83% align:start
leaving her young nephew
as the only rightful heir

00:13:36.183 --> 00:13:38.687 position:35% line:83% align:start
at the time
when his father died in the war.

00:13:38.852 --> 00:13:42.089 position:16% line:83% align:start
Lady Retes was to assume
the position as his regent,

00:13:42.222 --> 00:13:44.425 position:16% line:83% align:start
but only until her nephew
came of age.

00:13:44.559 --> 00:13:46.761 position:10% line:83% align:start
So, she's the current holder
of the fief?

00:13:46.894 --> 00:13:48.295 position:41% line:89% align:start
Mm-hmm.

00:13:48.429 --> 00:13:49.631 position:30% line:89% align:start
But tragically,

00:13:49.764 --> 00:13:52.667 position:13% line:83% align:start
her nephew died of illness
before he came of age.

00:13:52.801 --> 00:13:56.504 position:5% line:83% align:start
I am grateful to have this time
with you, Count Brioche Retes.

00:13:56.638 --> 00:13:57.938 position:21% line:89% align:start
The pleasure is mine.

00:13:58.405 --> 00:14:02.009 position:21% line:83% align:start
My! What an adorable
young gentleman.

00:14:04.178 --> 00:14:05.547 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
She seems cordial enough.

00:14:05.680 --> 00:14:09.551 position:19% line:83% align:start
But she is observing us
very closely.

00:14:10.918 --> 00:14:13.120 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[chuckles]
-[chuckles]

00:14:13.253 --> 00:14:15.790 position:21% line:83% align:start
Would the two of you
care to join me for tea?

00:14:15.923 --> 00:14:17.858 position:21% line:89% align:start
I would be delighted.

00:14:21.929 --> 00:14:23.897 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Ah, look at those!

00:14:24.031 --> 00:14:25.700 position:19% line:89% align:start
Baked treats, cookies?

00:14:25.834 --> 00:14:28.636 position:19% line:83% align:start
This tea is one of our
household businesses.

00:14:28.770 --> 00:14:31.673 position:30% line:83% align:start
We've prepared
only the finest for your visit.

00:14:31.806 --> 00:14:33.407 position:16% line:89% align:start
Your teas are well known.

00:14:33.541 --> 00:14:36.210 position:30% line:83% align:start
Even throughout
the royal capital, milady.

00:14:39.313 --> 00:14:40.914 position:21% line:89% align:start
Yes, truly excellent.

00:14:41.048 --> 00:14:42.349 position:21% line:89% align:start
The aroma and flavor

00:14:42.483 --> 00:14:44.485 position:30% line:83% align:start
both live up to
their reputation.

00:14:44.619 --> 00:14:47.254 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'm truly pleased to hear
you think so.

00:14:49.858 --> 00:14:52.627 position:10% line:83% align:start
[PAS] I used to make cookies
like this all the time!

00:14:52.761 --> 00:14:54.763 position:16% line:83% align:start
The time and temperature
before you bake them

00:14:54.895 --> 00:14:56.330 position:21% line:89% align:start
is what matters most!

00:14:56.463 --> 00:14:57.732 position:38% line:89% align:start
Ah, mm...

00:14:57.866 --> 00:14:59.900 position:35% line:89% align:start
[munching]

00:15:00.033 --> 00:15:01.935 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Hmm... It's kind of...

00:15:02.069 --> 00:15:02.970 position:41% line:83% align:start
[RETES]
Huh?

00:15:03.103 --> 00:15:04.471 position:13% line:89% align:start
Most children skip for joy

00:15:04.606 --> 00:15:06.574 position:16% line:83% align:start
when offered sweet things
of any kind.

00:15:06.708 --> 00:15:08.275 position:13% line:89% align:start
What's wrong with this boy?

00:15:08.409 --> 00:15:09.544 position:38% line:89% align:start
[slurps]

00:15:09.677 --> 00:15:11.278 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm!

00:15:11.412 --> 00:15:14.014 position:7% line:83% align:start
[RETES] I see you excel at more
than just military matters.

00:15:14.148 --> 00:15:15.315 position:24% line:89% align:start
You're quite famous

00:15:15.449 --> 00:15:17.117 position:33% line:83% align:start
for rendering
a barren land bountiful.

00:15:17.251 --> 00:15:18.352 position:16% line:89% align:start
That prompts me to think

00:15:18.485 --> 00:15:20.120 position:13% line:83% align:start
you're a wonderful leader,
as well.

00:15:20.254 --> 00:15:21.856 position:13% line:89% align:start
Thanks for the kind words.

00:15:21.989 --> 00:15:24.091 position:16% line:83% align:start
I strive hard to maintain
my own lands,

00:15:24.224 --> 00:15:25.492 position:21% line:89% align:start
but I'd love to hear

00:15:25.627 --> 00:15:27.194 position:13% line:83% align:start
about your administration's
agriculture.

00:15:27.327 --> 00:15:30.164 position:24% line:83% align:start
You have certainly
overestimated me, My Lady.

00:15:30.297 --> 00:15:31.699 position:16% line:89% align:start
You know, the real reason

00:15:31.833 --> 00:15:34.334 position:16% line:83% align:start
why the land can support
its people so well,

00:15:34.468 --> 00:15:36.937 position:10% line:83% align:start
is all because of the prowess
of my son!

00:15:37.070 --> 00:15:39.306 position:7% line:83% align:start
I myself have very little to do
with it.

00:15:39.440 --> 00:15:42.510 position:7% line:89% align:start
My, your son then? How humble.

00:15:42.644 --> 00:15:45.312 position:13% line:83% align:start
While I shamefully struggle
just to keep my lands together,

00:15:45.446 --> 00:15:47.916 position:16% line:83% align:start
you refuse to take pride
in your many accomplishments.

00:15:48.048 --> 00:15:49.283 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckles]

00:15:49.416 --> 00:15:51.418 position:41% line:83% align:start
I know,
normally no one would believe

00:15:51.553 --> 00:15:54.923 position:16% line:83% align:start
such a young child could
be leading territorial reform,

00:15:55.055 --> 00:15:58.192 position:19% line:83% align:start
and yet that's exactly
what he's doing.

00:15:59.026 --> 00:16:00.494 position:41% line:83% align:start
[RETES]
It must make you proud

00:16:00.628 --> 00:16:02.864 position:19% line:83% align:start
to have such a fine man
for a father.

00:16:02.996 --> 00:16:04.666 position:38% line:83% align:start
I'm sure
you want to be just like him.

00:16:04.799 --> 00:16:06.967 position:16% line:83% align:start
[PAS] The conversation's
finally turned to me.

00:16:07.100 --> 00:16:08.235 position:27% line:89% align:start
Now's my chance!

00:16:08.368 --> 00:16:10.137 position:21% line:89% align:start
Yes, I'm very proud.

00:16:10.270 --> 00:16:12.607 position:38% line:83% align:start
He's why
my family's so prosperous.

00:16:12.740 --> 00:16:14.576 position:21% line:89% align:start
Aw! I'm sure, he is.

00:16:15.677 --> 00:16:18.979 position:24% line:83% align:start
However, my father
poured himself into our fief

00:16:19.112 --> 00:16:21.081 position:24% line:83% align:start
and it has recently
been attacked.

00:16:21.215 --> 00:16:22.416 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:16:22.550 --> 00:16:24.151 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Over a 100 bandits showed up.

00:16:24.284 --> 00:16:26.253 position:10% line:83% align:start
Even I and my fellow children
were forced

00:16:26.386 --> 00:16:27.956 position:10% line:89% align:start
to take up swords and fight.

00:16:28.088 --> 00:16:29.323 position:41% line:83% align:start
[RETES]
Over a hundred?

00:16:29.456 --> 00:16:31.693 position:21% line:83% align:start
[PAS] It was actually
just around 50,

00:16:31.826 --> 00:16:34.428 position:30% line:83% align:start
but then again,
it's a strategic lie.

00:16:34.562 --> 00:16:37.397 position:33% line:83% align:start
Exaggeration
is a negotiator's trick.

00:16:37.532 --> 00:16:38.533 position:35% line:89% align:start
Damnation!

00:16:38.666 --> 00:16:40.835 position:30% line:83% align:start
I let the child
broach the subject.

00:16:41.636 --> 00:16:44.539 position:16% line:83% align:start
It's marvelous to see you
assuming the duties of nobility

00:16:44.672 --> 00:16:45.940 position:21% line:89% align:start
at such a young age.

00:16:46.073 --> 00:16:48.442 position:7% line:83% align:start
Our household could truly learn
from your example!

00:16:48.576 --> 00:16:51.813 position:10% line:83% align:start
Really? When we interrogated
the bandits we captured,

00:16:51.946 --> 00:16:55.015 position:33% line:83% align:start
they admitted
they'd come out of Retesvale.

00:16:55.482 --> 00:16:56.718 position:47% line:89% align:start
Uh?

00:16:57.217 --> 00:16:59.386 position:7% line:83% align:start
[RETES] He's going to negotiate
for damages.

00:16:59.521 --> 00:17:00.922 position:16% line:89% align:start
I should feign ignorance.

00:17:01.054 --> 00:17:04.258 position:10% line:83% align:start
Gracious, could that be true?
I hadn't heard that.

00:17:04.391 --> 00:17:05.927 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
If you doubt my words,

00:17:06.059 --> 00:17:09.196 position:10% line:83% align:start
we are prepared to hand over
some of the bandits to you.

00:17:09.731 --> 00:17:12.165 position:19% line:83% align:start
If that fails to spark
your memory,

00:17:12.299 --> 00:17:14.034 position:30% line:83% align:start
we'll just turn
them over to the king.

00:17:14.167 --> 00:17:15.369 position:24% line:89% align:start
